result.execSummary:
The defendant Jerry L Warfield was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jerry L Warfield is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jerry L Warfield was found guilty of Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater, Domestic Abuse Repeater], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Jerry L Warfield was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Prosecuting Atty Craig Lambert appeared for State of Wisconsin. Child Jaliyah S Warfield not in court. Mother Jasemine Logan not in court. Father Jerry Warfield appeared via phone. Wood County Human Services Social Worker Jill Vruwink in court. Michele Newman, Victim Witness Coordinator in court. Atty Nathan Oswald in court.

10:05 a.m. Lambert states case and appearances noting this is a combination of 3 cases: 19JC2, 15CF479 and 15CF169. He states the Dept is requesting a modification to the no contact order between Jasmine Logan and Jerry Warfield. 

Court asks States position. Atty Lambert speaks on the no contact order being appropriate due to history of domestic violence. States speaks on concerns of abuse and controlling behavior. He defers to the court if a mechanism/app would be appropriate - as long as it is monitored, need some type of oversight.

Court calls Jill V to the table. She discusses her conversations with Jasemine regarding the app.

Court speaks to Jerry W who states he is out of jail. Jill V states that he has visitation with Jaliyah 2x per week after school. 

Court states they never want the parents to have contact again - ever. Court states not inclined to offer app as mom is not here. Jill V states we are here today because Jasemine was told about the app in therapy. Court speaks on family wizard.  

Jerry Warfield speaks to the court.

Court will wait for letter from Jasemine before making a decision.

10:17 a.m. Court adjourns.

8:25 Defendant Jerry L Warfield in court with attorney Karl Alexander Schmidt.  Defendant Jerry L Warfield in custody.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Victim, J.L., makes statement.
Jury trial - 12 person at 03-30-2016 08:15 am
Jury trial - 12 person at 03-30-2016 08:15 am

3:41 Defendant Jerry L Warfield in court with attorney Karl Alexander Schmidt.  Defendant Jerry L Warfield in custody.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sari Goodness is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Lambert. On 12/25/15, she was dispatched to a disturbance at a residence in the City of Marshfield, Wood County. Their department received information from the Wood County Jail that the defendant was going to be released and he was saying that he was going to kidnap his daughter. J.L. had a restraining order against the defendant at the time. Testifies as to what J.L. told her happened that day. Testifies as to defendant coming to apartment building that day and was possibly armed. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. Attorney Schmidt cross-examines witness. Attorney Lambert redirects. 
Attorney Lambert asks Court take judicial notice of Wood County cases 15CV210, 15CF169, 14CM229. Court takes judicial notice. 
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bound over for further proceedings. Bond is continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for February 5, 2016 at 09:00 am.
